<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1437,448,943]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,737,763]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1930" box="[645,806,736,762]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komonensis">
<emphasis box="[645,806,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P. komonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1142,736,762]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternans">
<emphasis box="[1006,1142,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P. alternans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1234,1432,736,762]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Zhou, H. - Z." box="[151,430,772,799]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="153 - 189" refId="ref79412" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Zhou, H. - Z. (2006) Leaf-rolling sawflies of the Pamphilius komonensis complex (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 32, 153 - 189." type="journal article" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Zhou 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1991" box="[449,715,772,798]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kyutekparki">
<emphasis box="[449,715,772,798]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Pamphilius kyutekparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to the Japanese 
<taxonomicName authority="Takeuchi, 1930" authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komonensis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1320,772,798]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P. komonensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Takeuchi, K." pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="3 - 16" refId="ref80368" refString="Takeuchi, K. (1930) A revisional list of the Japanese Pamphiliidae, with description of nine new species. Transactions of the Kansai Entomological Society, 1, 3 - 16." type="journal article" year="1930">Takeuchi, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, though the two allopatric taxa are separated at least by the color pattern (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1035,1230,808,835]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="25 - 63" refId="ref76426" refString="Shinohara, A. (1991 a) Pamphilius alternans (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 17, 25 - 63." type="journal article" year="1991">Shinohara 1991a</bibRefCitation>
). In our molecular analysis using COI and NaK sequences, the two species were not clearly differentiated (
<figureCitation box="[1156,1258,844,871]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–141" captionStartId="229.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,186,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-19@229.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="229" captionText="FIGURES 140–141: Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 140. alternans group. 141. basilaris group." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Figs 140</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1271,1317,844,871]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–155" captionStartId="241.[151,264,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,188,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-19@241.[151,1436,181,1753]" captionTargetPageId="241" captionText="FIGURES 154–155: Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 154. alternans group. 155. basilaris group." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">154</figureCitation>
). The host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1991" box="[247,406,880,906]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kyutekparki">
<emphasis box="[247,406,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P. kyutekparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still unknown, but it is probably 
<taxonomicName box="[811,864,881,907]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[811,864,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Acer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[880,1026,880,906]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
), which is the host of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shinohara &amp; Okutani 1983)" baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Okutani" baseAuthorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komonensis">
<emphasis box="[1277,1437,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P. komonensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Okutani, T." box="[159,467,916,943]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="276 - 281" refId="ref78722" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Okutani, T. (1983) Host-plants of Japanese Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Kontyu, Tokyo, 51, 276 - 281." type="journal article" year="1983">Shinohara &amp; Okutani 1983</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
